# Complete RMBS Structural Benefit Analysis
## Step-by-Step Walkthrough with All Formulas

---

# Part 1: Understanding What We're Isolating

## The Three Variables

When comparing two RMBS transactions, the cost of funding difference comes from three sources:

```
Total WACOF Difference = Credit Effect + Pricing Effect + Structure Effect
```

| Variable | What It Represents | What Changed It |
|----------|-------------------|-----------------|
| Credit Quality | WAFF × WALS by rating category | Different collateral pool |
| Market Pricing | Tranche margins at each rating | Market conditions, investor demand |
| Structure | Tranche sizes, CE levels, reserve sizing | Your structuring decisions |

**Your goal:** Prove that even if credit and pricing were identical, your structure delivers savings.

---

# Part 2: Setting Up the Data

## Sample Data — Old Deal (Previous Transaction)

### Collateral Characteristics (Old Deal)

| Metric | Value |
|--------|-------|
| Pool Balance | £500,000,000 |
| Weighted Average LTV | 72% |
| Weighted Average Seasoning | 24 months |
| % Owner Occupied | 85% |
| % BTL | 15% |
| Geographic Concentration (London/SE) | 45% |

### Rating Agency Credit Assumptions (Old Deal)

| Rating Level | WAFF | WALS | WAFF × WALS |
|--------------|------|------|-------------|
| AAA | 12.5% | 28.0% | 3.50% |
| AA | 9.2% | 24.5% | 2.25% |
| A | 6.8% | 21.0% | 1.43% |
| BBB | 4.5% | 18.0% | 0.81% |
| BB | 2.8% | 15.0% | 0.42% |

### Capital Structure (Old Deal)

| Tranche | Rating | Size (%) | Size (£m) | CE (%) | Margin (SONIA+) |
|---------|--------|----------|-----------|--------|-----------------|
| A | AAA | 85.0% | 425.0 | 15.0% | 85 bps |
| B | AA | 5.0% | 25.0 | 10.0% | 130 bps |
| C | A | 4.0% | 20.0 | 6.0% | 175 bps |
| D | BBB | 3.0% | 15.0 | 3.0% | 275 bps |
| E | BB | 1.5% | 7.5 | 1.5% | 475 bps |
| Z/Equity | NR | 1.5% | 7.5 | 0.0% | Residual |
| **Total Rated** | | **98.5%** | **492.5** | | |

### Reserve Fund (Old Deal)

| Item | Value |
|------|-------|
| Initial Reserve | 1.5% of notes = £7.39m |
| Target Reserve | 1.5% of notes |
| Reserve Fund Amortisation | None (fixed) |

