# Part 15: Sensitivity Analysis

## What If Credit Were Identical?

| Scenario | WACOF |
|----------|-------|
| Old Structure, Old Credit, Old Pricing | 102.66 bps |
| New Structure, Old Credit, Old Pricing | 98.67 bps |
| **Pure Structural Benefit** | **3.99 bps** |

## What If Pricing Were Identical?

| Scenario | WACOF |
|----------|-------|
| Old Structure, Old Credit, New Pricing | 88.05 bps |
| New Structure, New Credit, New Pricing | 83.64 bps |
| **Improvement (Credit + Structure)** | **4.41 bps** |

---

# Summary of All Key Formulas

## Credit Metrics

```
WAFF × WALS = Expected Loss at each rating level

CE Multiple = Credit Enhancement / (WAFF × WALS)
```

## Funding Cost Metrics

```
WACOF = Σ(Tranche Size × Margin) / Total Rated %

Annual Cost = WACOF (bps) × Notes Outstanding / 10,000

NPV Saving = Annual Saving × PV Annuity Factor
```

## Normalisation Formulas

```
Normalised CE = CE Multiple × Baseline WAFF × WALS

Credit Effect = WACOF(old) − WACOF(old structure, new credit)

Pricing Effect = WACOF(new credit) − WACOF(new credit, new pricing)

Structure Effect = Total Improvement − Credit Effect − Pricing Effect
```

## Advance Rate

```
Advance Rate = Rated Notes / Pool Balance × 100%

Additional Proceeds = Advance Rate Improvement × Pool Balance
```

---

This framework provides a complete, defensible methodology for demonstrating structural value-add to your sponsor client. Shall I refine any specific section or add additional scenarios?